Introduction

Hwang Minhyun is a South Korean singer and actor under Pledis Entertainment. He is the lead vocalist of the boy group NU'EST and a former member of the temporary boy group Wanna One. Minhyun is best known for competing in the second season of MNET's Produce 101 where he earned a spot to be a member of Wanna One. After the group's success and disbandment, Minhyun returned to the group NU'EST.

Minhyun debuted as a member of the boy group NU'EST in 2012.

Wanna One debuted on August 7, 2017, with their first mini album 1X1=1 (To Be One), and officially concluded their activities on January 27, 2019.

Following Wanna One's disbandment, he released his first digital single "Universe" on April 3, 2019.

On June 26, 2020, Hwang was cast in the lead role of Go Eun-taek in the JTBC drama Live On, which aired from November 2020 to January 2021.

On February 28, Pledis Entertainment announced that the NU'EST members' contracts would expire on March 14 and Minhyun decided to renew with the company.

On February 27, 2023, He made his solo debut, with the mini album Truth or Lie.
